14:03.111 --> 14:06.214
BARNEY:
Okay, Neruda, this play is

14:06.216 --> 14:07.698
extremely complicated.

14:07.700 --> 14:09.116
Let me guess.
Does it involve me

14:09.118 --> 14:11.202
saying "my penis"
in a Scottish accent?

14:11.204 --> 14:13.170
(Scottish accent):
Now you're gettin' it, laddie!

14:14.540 --> 14:15.590
Hey!

14:15.592 --> 14:17.041
Robin. What are you doing here?

14:17.043 --> 14:18.342
I was curious as to whether

14:18.344 --> 14:20.044
you found Ted a date
to our wedding

14:20.046 --> 14:22.179
who was a little less,
you know, Antichrist-y.

14:25.634 --> 14:27.418
Is that the Playbook?

14:27.420 --> 14:32.590
No, Robin, that is a couch.

14:40.432 --> 14:42.733
Oh, you mean
the Playbook <i>on</i> the couch?

14:42.735 --> 14:43.734
I can explain.

14:43.736 --> 14:44.768
Don't bother.

14:44.770 --> 14:46.787
I can ex...
Uh, Ted? Uh...

14:46.789 --> 14:48.489
I got to step away from
mission control for a sec.

14:48.491 --> 14:50.441
Don't do anything stupid
while I'm gone.

14:50.443 --> 14:52.109
Robin...

14:52.111 --> 14:54.295
(no dialogue)

15:04.878 --> 15:06.662
Robin, wait.

15:07.589 --> 15:09.288
Um... shoot.
I haven't figured out

15:09.290 --> 15:11.424
what I'm gonna say yet.
Keep going.

15:13.294 --> 15:14.811
Robin, wait.

15:16.146 --> 15:18.598
Look, I'm sorry
that I still have the Playbook.

15:18.600 --> 15:21.100
It's just, it's filled
with a lifetime of great ideas.

15:21.102 --> 15:23.186
Am I supposed to just
leave all that behind?

15:23.188 --> 15:25.438
Yes.
But...

15:25.440 --> 15:27.690
"Weekend at Barney's"!

15:27.692 --> 15:28.858
Okay, what is that?

15:28.860 --> 15:31.160
Explain the
"Weekend at Barney's" to me.

15:31.162 --> 15:32.161
What's to explain?

15:32.163 --> 15:33.279
I play a dead guy,

15:33.281 --> 15:34.814
and Ted and Marshall
carry me around.

15:34.816 --> 15:36.866
Okay. And based on that,
girls want to sleep with you.

15:36.868 --> 15:38.334
Big time.
But you're dead.

15:38.336 --> 15:40.503
Yeah. Except not really,
obviously.

15:40.505 --> 15:41.921
But the girl thinks you're dead.

15:41.923 --> 15:42.923
No, she thinks I'm alive.

15:42.924 --> 15:44.040
Which you are.
Exactly.

15:44.042 --> 15:45.792
Except you're dead.
Exactly.

15:45.794 --> 15:47.493
Except you're alive.
Exactly.

15:47.495 --> 15:50.179
Okay, so instead of...
of being an alive person

15:50.181 --> 15:52.048
pretending to be a dead person

15:52.050 --> 15:53.600
pretending to be
an alive person,

15:53.602 --> 15:56.185
why not just be an alive person?

15:57.087 --> 15:59.606
Okay, let's start
from the beginning.

15:59.608 --> 16:03.726
The movie is called
<i>Weekend at Bernie's.</i>

16:03.728 --> 16:06.512
My name is Barney.

16:07.898 --> 16:09.699
I'm so sorry,
sweetie.

16:09.701 --> 16:11.067
I don't know
if you heard,

16:11.069 --> 16:12.402
but I dropped
some Skittles.

16:12.404 --> 16:13.486
Do you know what,
I'm just gonna

16:13.488 --> 16:14.787
go home before I
make things worse.

16:14.789 --> 16:16.456
You're not
going anywhere.

16:16.458 --> 16:17.624
We're a team.

16:17.626 --> 16:18.574
You stuck by me

16:18.576 --> 16:20.410
after my nip slip

16:20.412 --> 16:22.045
at your law school graduation.

16:22.047 --> 16:25.298
And after my nip slip
at the GNB Christmas party.

16:25.300 --> 16:26.716
And after my nip slip

16:26.718 --> 16:29.052
at the Honeywell and Coots
Family Fun Day.

16:29.054 --> 16:31.170
I don't know why you
keep wearing that top.

16:31.172 --> 16:32.805
All right,
I'll stay put,

16:32.807 --> 16:34.173
but I'm keeping
my mouth shut.

16:34.175 --> 16:37.260
No more jokes,
no more candy,

16:37.262 --> 16:39.312
no more Teenage
Mutant Ninja Turtles.

16:39.314 --> 16:41.047
Hey, are you guys
talking Ninja Turtles?

16:41.765 --> 16:43.516
I'm a huge TMNT fan.

16:43.518 --> 16:45.184
I grew up on those comic books.

16:45.186 --> 16:47.520
Me, too!
I was obsessed.

16:47.522 --> 16:49.605
Did you know that
the original comic debuted

16:49.607 --> 16:51.941
in 1984 at a convention
in New Hampshire?

16:51.943 --> 16:53.392
Uh, yes.

16:53.394 --> 16:55.561
Did you know that Eastman and
Laird always had their doubts

16:55.563 --> 16:56.996
about their characters
being commercialized?

16:56.998 --> 16:58.197
Yes!

16:58.199 --> 16:59.999
Did you know that the painting
on the back wall

17:00.001 --> 17:01.501
is inspired by Master Splinter?

17:02.453 --> 17:05.003
Oh, the one of the
rat doing karate.

17:05.006 --> 17:06.955
I see it now.

17:06.958 --> 17:08.124
Hey, I'm Strickland.

17:08.126 --> 17:09.575
Hey. Marshall.

17:09.577 --> 17:12.462
And this is my wife, Lily,
who, as a matter of fact,

17:12.464 --> 17:14.597
happens to represent one of
the biggest art collectors

17:14.598 --> 17:15.682
in New York City.

17:15.684 --> 17:16.965
I love your work.

17:16.968 --> 17:19.585
It's great to see you
getting some recognition.

17:19.587 --> 17:21.420
Thank you.
It's been a long haul.

17:21.422 --> 17:23.388
The first painting
I ever sold,

17:23.391 --> 17:26.476
I used the money
to get my car fixed.

17:26.478 --> 17:28.144
You might say...

17:28.146 --> 17:31.097
I used it to make my <i>van go.</i>

17:31.099 --> 17:32.398
(laughing):
That's...

17:32.400 --> 17:34.283
(laughing)

17:34.285 --> 17:37.370
Um, a little something
called rigor mortis?

17:37.372 --> 17:38.771
Oh, come on.

17:38.773 --> 17:40.773
Are you really this
mad about a book?

17:40.775 --> 17:43.943
You really think that this
is just about a book, Barney?

17:44.745 --> 17:45.661
You lied to me.

17:45.663 --> 17:47.113
If we're gonna
be in a marriage

17:47.115 --> 17:49.582
and trust each other,
you can't lie to me ever.

17:49.584 --> 17:50.666
Really?

17:50.668 --> 17:52.118
Well, that's just great.

17:52.120 --> 17:55.254
Because, in case you haven't
noticed these last eight years,

17:55.256 --> 17:57.390
lying is what I do best.

17:59.143 --> 18:00.459
I'm a magician, Robin.

18:00.461 --> 18:04.630
Misdirection and deceit
are my stock in trade.

18:04.632 --> 18:06.382
You don't want me
to lie to you?

18:06.384 --> 18:09.102
Lies are the reason
that we're together.

18:09.104 --> 18:10.970
Everything single
thing I did

18:10.972 --> 18:13.239
to get you to say yes
to me on that rooftop--

18:13.241 --> 18:15.575
Patrice, the false
engagement, everything--

18:15.577 --> 18:17.827
it was all utter malarkey.

18:17.829 --> 18:18.911
But...

18:18.913 --> 18:20.997
underneath all
of those lies

18:20.999 --> 18:23.199
is one true thing.

18:23.201 --> 18:26.202
One true thing
that can support the weight

18:26.204 --> 18:29.288
of all the lies
in the world, and...

18:29.290 --> 18:31.290
and that's the fact
that I love you.

18:31.292 --> 18:32.608
And you know

18:32.610 --> 18:34.177
that when I say that...

18:34.179 --> 18:35.678
I am not lying.

18:45.505 --> 18:46.689
Wha...

18:57.367 --> 18:58.868
Did you just unhook
my bra again?

18:58.870 --> 19:00.119
(Barney shushes)

19:00.121 --> 19:01.220
TED:
<i>Jeanette,</i>

19:01.222 --> 19:02.488
this is great.

19:02.490 --> 19:03.856
We're back together.

19:03.858 --> 19:06.542
You're coming to Barney
and Robin's wedding.

19:06.544 --> 19:09.495
I found two wine glasses
you didn't smash.

19:09.497 --> 19:11.547
Call me crazy,
but I've got a feeling,

19:11.549 --> 19:14.300
from here on out, it's gonna be
nothing but blue skies and...

19:14.302 --> 19:15.251
What...

19:15.253 --> 19:16.702
the hell...

19:16.704 --> 19:18.421
is this?!

19:19.306 --> 19:20.923
(cell phone chiming)

19:20.925 --> 19:22.058
Uh-oh.

19:22.060 --> 19:23.726
Check out this
text from Ted.

19:23.728 --> 19:25.595
(sighs)

19:29.166 --> 19:30.366
Oh, my...

19:30.368 --> 19:32.235
What the hell
happened here?

19:32.237 --> 19:34.403
Jeanette and I had
a little spat.

19:35.372 --> 19:36.489
(cuckoos)

19:36.491 --> 19:37.990
Would anyone like some wine?

19:37.992 --> 19:39.525
It's a nice Côtes du Rhne.

19:39.527 --> 19:41.027
Still needs to breathe a bit.

19:41.029 --> 19:43.496
You know what?
I got a decanter upstairs, so...

19:44.564 --> 19:47.233
We should just drink it now.

19:47.235 --> 19:48.501
JEANETTE:
And for

19:48.503 --> 19:49.702
the grand finale,

19:49.704 --> 19:51.237
I found your fireworks.

19:51.239 --> 19:53.372
Let's see what they do
to your precious Playbook!

19:53.374 --> 19:54.573
TED:
No!

19:54.575 --> 19:55.675
Jeanette, please,

19:55.677 --> 19:57.360
that's Barney's
life's work!

19:57.362 --> 19:58.744
BARNEY:
It's fine, Ted.

19:59.930 --> 20:01.264
Blow it up, Jeanette.

20:01.266 --> 20:05.685
♪ Put a candle in the window

20:09.139 --> 20:13.759
♪ 'Cause I feel
I've got to move ♪

20:17.231 --> 20:21.200
♪ Though I'm going, going

20:21.202 --> 20:24.453
♪ I'll be coming home soon

20:24.455 --> 20:28.291
♪ Long as I can see
the light... ♪

20:38.135 --> 20:39.969
Okay.

20:39.971 --> 20:42.471
No more dating.

20:42.473 --> 20:44.340
I'm ready to settle down.

20:44.342 --> 20:45.758
NARRATOR:
<i>And, kids...</i>

20:45.760 --> 20:47.176
for the first time in my life,

20:47.178 --> 20:48.678
<i>I really meant it.</i>

20:48.680 --> 20:49.628
Oh!

20:49.630 --> 20:51.681
MARSHALL: Oh...
The boots...

20:51.683 --> 20:53.099
(laughing)

20:53.101 --> 20:54.400
(groans)

